Description :
Processes a string and removes the player name(max len 99) You can use this function to create notifications/subtitles -------------------------------------------------------------------- Usage(Colors) :
~r~ = red ~y~ = yellow ~g~ = green ~b~ = light blue ~w~ = white ~p~ = purple ~n~ = new line
-------------------------------------------------------------------- Usage(Input) : ~INPUT_CONTEXT~ will show button symbol (regarding last input device - keyboard/gamepad) example: string info = Context action is assigned to ~INPUT_CONTEXT~!;
-------------------------------------------------------------------- Example (C++):
void ShowNotification(char text) { UI::_SET_NOTIFICATION_TEXT_ENTRY(STRING); UI::ADD_TEXT_COMPONENT_SUBSTRING_PLAYER_NAME(text); UI::_DRAW_NOTIFICATION(FALSE, FALSE); // if first param = 1, the message flashes 1 or 2 times }
Colors example :
string red = ~r~Red test; string white_and_yellow = ~w~White and ~y~yellow; string text_with_double_line = First line.~n~Second line;
This native (along with 0x5F68520888E69014 and 0x94CF4AC034C9C986) do not actually filter anything. They simply add the provided text (as of 944)
